TITLE: Creating a 3D Cartesian Coordinate System with Axes
DESCRIPTION: JavaScript code that sets up a 3D Cartesian coordinate system with specific range and scale, then adds x and y axes to the visualization.
SOURCE: https://github.com/unconed/mathbox/blob/master/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const view = root
  .cartesian({
    range: [
      [-2, 2],
      [-1, 1],
      [-1, 1],
    ],
    scale: [2, 1, 1],
  })
  .axis({
    axis: 1,
  })
  .axis({
    axis: 2,
  });
```

