TITLE: Implementing Animation with MathBox Play Element in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to create an animation using the MathBox play element. It defines keyframes to animate the graph's range, sets the animation pace, duration, and looping behavior.
SOURCE: https://github.com/unconed/mathbox/blob/master/docs/intro.md#2025-04-22_snippet_19

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
var play = mathbox.play({
  target: 'cartesian',
  pace: 5,
  to: 2,
  loop: true,
  script: [
    {props: {range: [[-2, 2], [-1, 1]]}},
    {props: {range: [[-4, 4], [-2, 2]]}},
    {props: {range: [[-2, 2], [-1, 1]]}},
  ]
});
```

