TITLE: Creating Vector Data and Visualization
DESCRIPTION: Creates a new interval that emits paired points (start and end positions) to represent vectors, and visualizes them as green arrows.
SOURCE: https://github.com/unconed/mathbox/blob/master/docs/intro.md#2025-04-22_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
var vector =
  view.interval({
    expr: function (emit, x, i, t) {
      emit(x, 0);
      emit(x, -Math.sin(x + t));
    },
    width: 64,
    channels: 2,
    items: 2,
  })
  .vector({
    end: true,
    width: 5,
    color: '#50A000',
  });
```

