TITLE: Implementing Temporal Blur in GLSL for MathBox
DESCRIPTION: A shader that implements temporal blur by averaging samples from the current position and three consecutive positions. It takes an intensity uniform parameter and returns a transformed color value based on the average intensity.
SOURCE: https://github.com/unconed/mathbox/blob/master/docs/shaders.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: glsl
CODE:
```
uniform float intensity;

vec4 getSample(vec3 xyz);
vec4 getFramesSample(vec3 xyz) {
  vec4 color = (
    getSample(xyz) +
    getSample(xyz + vec3(0.0, 0.0, 1.0)) +
    getSample(xyz + vec3(0.0, 0.0, 2.0)) +
    getSample(xyz + vec3(0.0, 0.0, 3.0))
  ) / 4.0;
  float v = (color.x + color.y + color.z) * intensity;
  return vec4(vec3(v * v) / 8.0, 1.0);
}
```

